Package importedImplementations.TinSpinIndexes.index.qtplain

Class QuadTreeKD0<T>

java.lang.Object
importedImplementations.TinSpinIndexes.index.qtplain.QuadTreeKD0<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Value type.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Index, PointMap<T>, PointMultimap<T>
public class QuadTreeKD0<T> extends Object implements PointMap<T>, PointMultimap<T>
A simple MX-quadtree implementation with configurable maximum depth, maximum nodes size, and (if desired) automatic guessing of root rectangle.

This version of the quadtree stores for each node only the center point and the distance (radius) to the edges. This reduces space requirements but increases problems with numerical precision. Overall it is more space efficient and slightly faster.

Author:
ztilmann
